================================================================================
Third-party attributions
================================================================================

The context-compression subsystem (internal/tools/filter.go,
internal/tools/compress.go, the embedded filters under
internal/tools/filters/, and the /discover report) re-implements, in Go,
ideas and patterns from two Apache-2.0 projects:

  * RTK — https://github.com/rtk-ai/rtk
      The declarative command-output filter format (match_command,
      strip_ansi, strip_lines_matching, max_lines, on_empty, and the inline
      per-filter tests), the per-command "failures-only" compaction approach,
      and the "discover uncovered commands" report are adapted from RTK.

  * headroom — https://github.com/chopratejas/headroom
      The structural diff/log/JSON compression approach, the token-aware
      "never inflate" guard, and the cache-boundary stability invariants are
      adapted from headroom.

Both projects are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0:

